  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-potato-topped-chicken-mustard-kale-pie/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whisk&nbsp;the<strong> Dijon mustard</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>cream</strong>&nbsp;<strong>cheese</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>cornflour</strong> with the<strong> chicken stock&nbsp;</strong>until smooth - this is your<strong> cooking sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-potato-topped-chicken-mustard-kale-pie/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>kale</strong>,<strong> diced&nbsp;chicken</strong> and <strong>cooking sauce</strong>&nbsp;to a <strong>wide</strong>&nbsp;<strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and season with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good old mix up and set aside</p>\r\n<p>Tip: use individual pie dishes for fancy presentation</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-potato-topped-chicken-mustard-kale-pie/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grate the<strong> cheddar cheese&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on)&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-potato-topped-chicken-mustard-kale-pie/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze any excess water out of the <strong>grated potatoes&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: wrap the grated potatoes in a clean tea towel and twist the cloth to remove as much water as possible</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-potato-topped-chicken-mustard-kale-pie/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Mix the <strong>grated potatoes</strong> and<strong> cheddar cheese</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-potato-topped-chicken-mustard-kale-pie/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>chicken</strong> and <strong>kale mixture</strong> with the <strong>grated potatoes&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 45-50 min or until golden and crispy and the chicken is cooked through&ndash; this is your<strong>&nbsp;potato-topped chicken, mustard &amp; kale pie&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/easy-potato-topped-chicken-mustard-kale-pie/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the tray from the oven and leave the<strong>&nbsp;pie</strong> to&nbsp;cool&nbsp;slightly for a few min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Serve the<strong>&nbsp;potato-topped&nbsp;chicken, mustard &amp; kale pie</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
